        "• 40.7 - Customer Engagement Window (including Cluster Study Project List, Scoping Meeting, and Physical \nInfeasibility Screening)/ Phase 1 Entry Decision Period\n[...]\nCommercial Readiness Deposits \nTo enter Phase 1 \n(Readiness Deposit 1) \nDue during Decision Period 1\n$4,000/MW\n[...]\nTo enter Phase 2 \n(Readiness Deposit 2)\n[...]\nDue during Decision Period\n[...]\nReadiness Deposit 1, and\n[...]\n20% of cost estimate \ndetermined in Phase 1 \n(\n[...]\n1 cost estimates \ninclude: Local SUF and \nCTOAF)\n[...]\n▪ Withdrawal Penalty 1 - If a project withdraws during the Customer Engagement Window or at \nthe Decision Point to Enter Phase 1, it forfeits 25% of its Study Deposit.\n[...]\n▪ Withdrawal Penalty 2 -If a project withdraws during Phase 1 or at the Decision Point at the \nconclusion of Phase 1, it forfeits an amount equal to 50% of the Study Deposit and 10% of \nthe Readiness Deposit 1.\n[...]\n▪ Withdrawal Penalty 3 -If a project withdraws during Phase 2 or at\n[...]\nDecision Point at the \nconclusion of Phase 2, it forfeits an amount equal to 100% of the Study Deposit and 20% of \nthe Readiness Deposit 2.\n[...]\nEngagement Window) to $5,000\n[...]\n▪ Reduce Withdrawal Penalty 2 (at end of Phase 1) amount to 25% of the Study Deposit (vs. 50% of \nthe Study Deposit plus 10% of the Readiness Deposit 1)\n[...]\n) amount to\n[...]\nStudy Deposit (\n[...]\n% of\n[...]\n% of the Readiness Deposit 2)\n[...]\n▪ To proceed to the Phase 2 Study, the Interconnection Customer must, in\n[...]\ndecision period following\n[...]\nthe Phase 1 Study: \n• Accept or reject its Project Cost Allocation determined in Phase 1; and\n[...]\n• Satisfy the Readiness Deposit 2 requirements.\n[...]\n▪ As described on Slide 49, the Readiness Deposit 2 is calculated as the greater of (i) the Readiness \nDeposit 1, and (ii) 20% of cost estimate determined in\n[...]\nPhase 1 Study less study \ndeposits/Commercial Readiness Deposit already posted (to enter Phase 1).\n[...