        "• 40.10 - Phase 1 Study/ Existing System Representation/ Annual Transmission Baseline Assessment / Phase 1 Study Scope and Procedures/ Phase 2 Entry \nDecision Period\n[...]\nReadiness Deposits (RD) /Security Amounts Withdrawal Penalty (WP) Amounts\n[...]\n0/MW\n[...]\nIf a project withdraws during the Application Window or up to within 5 Business Days of the \nNYISO publishing the cluster member list in the Customer Engagement Window, there is no \nwithdrawal penalty. Also. no withdrawal penalty for contingent projects and projects that \nwithdraw due to physical infeasibility\n[...]\nWP1 25% of SD, except if withdrawal is of a contingent project or due to physical infeasibility\n[...]\nWP2 50% of SD + 10% of RD1, except if withdrawal is due to physical infeasibility\n[...]\nWP3 100% of SD +20% of RD2, except if withdrawal is due to physical infeasibility or if there has \nbeen a 50% cost increase between Phase 1 and Phase 2 (non SDU) costs.\n[...]\n Study Deposits and Commercial Readiness Deposits can be submitted as cash or through a Letter of Credit \n• Att HH will detail cash and Letter of Credit deposit requirements.\n[...]\n Applicable Study Deposit and Commercial Readiness Deposit will remain in place for \nduration of the Cluster Study Process and will be subject to withdrawal penalties as \ndescribed in slides 94-99.\n[...]\n If, at the completion of Phase 2 of the Cluster Study Process, Interconnection Customer \naccepts its cost allocation and posts security, the NYISO will refund the full amount of \nboth the Study Deposit and Commercial Readiness Deposit (after final invoicing and \npayment of study costs).\n[...]\nCommercial Readiness Deposits \nTo enter Phase 1 \n(Readiness Deposit 1) \nDue during Decision Period 1\n[...]\n$4,000/MW\n[...]\nTo enter Phase 2 \n(Readiness Deposit 2) \nDue during Decision Period 2"
